By Kolade Adeyemi, Kano  Three COVID-19 patients are on the run in Kano. The Coordinator of Kano Taskforce on COVID 19, Dr Tijjani Hussain, disclosed this to The Nation. He said the three coronavirus patients disappeared from their respective houses and have been unreachable. According to him, the patients have switched off their phones with their homes deserted. He said that they must have relocated elsewhere, declaring the Task Force was in search of them. Hussain said: “We are collaborating with security agents to track them and bring them to the isolation centre.” Kano has 77 confirmed cases with one recorded death. Details shortly…